OL,3,CAirlines cut two million seats: How
OL,4,Cwill this affect summer travel plans?
OL,6,FKenton Jarvis, CEO of easyJet, said:
OL,7,F"We are operating as normal and are
OL,8,Fnot making changes or cancellations
OL,9,Fand we are looking forward to taking
OL,10,Fmillions of people on their well-
OL,11,Fdeserved holidays this summer."
OL,13,FRyanair similarly says no flights have
OL,14,Fbeen cancelled due to fuel shortages.
OL,16,FWizz Air has also confirmed it plans
OL,17,Fto continue to operate its full summer
OL,18,Fschedule, "flying passengers safely
OL,19,Fand reliably to their destinations
OL,20,Facross its extensive network".
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
